th-buff-debuff-tracker-summary-section{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:.35em}.health-buff-debuff-tracker-summary-section h3{margin:0 0 .1em}.health-buff-debuff-tracker-empty-state{display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:.5em;padding:2em;border:1px dashed rgba(127,127,127,.4);border-radius:8px;background:rgba(127,127,127,.04);color:rgba(127,127,127,.8)}.health-buff-debuff-tracker-empty-state svg{fill:currentColor}.health-buff-debuff-tracker-dynamic-table .hyper-table-container{margin-top:0!important;padding-top:0!important}.health-buff-debuff-tracker-checkin-details p,.health-buff-debuff-tracker-medicine-section p,.health-buff-debuff-tracker-summary-section p{margin:0;padding:0}","tags":"$:/tags/Stylesheet","type":"text/css"},"$:/TraitTag/OPMI/Status":{"created":"20230219143648537","text":"OPMI is a biomedical ontology in the area of precision medicine and its related investigations. It is community-driven and developed by following the OBO Foundry ontology development principles.
In OPMI, we treated medical condition status as a status, which is a realizable entitry. One major section of the branch is various diagnosis condition status. There are basically two types of diagnosis: one type diagnosis is treated as a condition status, the other is diagnosis (OGMS_0000073) as a type of clinical data item. One good example to illustrate the difference is the difference between primary and principal diagnoses. While these can be (and frequently are) the same diagnosis in practice, their definitions are distinct. While a principal diagnosis is the underlying cause of patient symptoms, the primary diagnosis is used for healthcare billing purposes and is a type of medical condition status. Reference: https://www.definitivehc.com/resources/glossary/primary-diagnosis","title":"$:/TraitTag/OPMI/Status","tags":"$:/SuperTag/TraitTag","type":"text/vnd.tiddlywiki","modified":"20241022164222277","url":"https://oscaf.sourceforge.net/tmo.html#tmo:Task","schema":"{
  "type": "object",
