!! Basic Usage

# Provide a <<lingo ShortName>> layout, use `ctrl+shift+L` to switch to this view
## or open it using a layout launcher like <<lingo ShortName $:/plugins/linonetwo/simple-layout-launcher/language/>> on the sidebar
# When the layout opens, there are a few buttons at the top
## On the left is a series of add buttons that, when clicked, jump back to the default layout and add new tiddlers
## On the right are buttons that jump directly back to the default layout
# Once you've added a few tiddlers, a table of data is displayed at the bottom of the layout, listing the tiddlers you've added.
## Clicking on the title of a tiddler in the table will jump back to the default layout and open that entry

!! Tags

The following tags are used in this entry to indicate that the entry records a symptom or health condition, the add button actually creates the entry with these tags:

<$list filter="[[$:/plugins/linonetwo/health-buff-debuff-tracker/tags/debuff]] [[$:/plugins/linonetwo/health-buff-debuff-tracker/tags/buff]] [[$:/plugins/linonetwo/health-buff-debuff-tracker/tags/medicine]] [[$:/plugins/linonetwo/health-buff-debuff-tracker/tags/condition]]">

  <$macrocall $name="tag" tag={{!!text}} /> {{!!caption}} - {{!!description}}

</$list>

You can make your own [ext[SuperTag|https://github.com/tiddly-gittly/super-tag/]] by adding [[$:/TraitTag/OPMI/Status]] tags to any tiddler.

Medical Condition Status: The state or status at the point during the visit the diagnosis was given (admitting diagnosis, final diagnosis), whether the diagnosis was determined due to laboratory findings, if the diagnosis was exclusionary, or if it was a preliminary diagnosis, among others.
